    CliSession

    public class TelnetSession
extends Object
implements CliSession
    A telnet transport. Example: 
     TelnetSession c = new TelnetSession("127.0.0.1", 23);

        public TelnetSession(NedWorker worker)
              throws IOException
        Constructor for Telnet session object. This method creates a a new telnet session on top of an existing connection. Telnet objects implement the Transport interface and they are passed into the constructor of the NetconfSession class.

      • ready

        public boolean ready()
              throws IOException
        Tell whether this transport is ready to be read.
        Returns:
        true if there is something to read, false otherwise. This function can typically be used to poll a socket and see there is data to be read. Note that this method does not detect that the socket is in half-closed state and in such case will return false after timeout.
        Throws:
        IOException
